values: This is probably the only chance I'll have to update in a very long time, so I'd just like to say..

Disclaimer.. 
We should all hope and look towards the day 
Where man realizes the sounds exiting his mouth 
Are mostly complaints and a change occurs

Say it, say it

Along you support
Then embrace another reason to see
Success we unfold
Clutching firm, betting he panics for sure

Say it, say it, that it's done
I want it, want it, need it done

The lie, want to know
Has it met, expectations so far

Say it, say it, that it's done
I want it, want it, need it done

Still running..
Never waking up to say it

Selfishly walking through
Killing the angles
Picking and choosing to
Screw all of us one by one

So run, make amends
Feeling torn
Boy, you better be sure

Still running..
Never waking up to say it

I can't sleep.

So my mom didn't pay the phone bill. Now I can't get online at home. Dial-up sucks.

I cleaned my room a few days ago. I'm a very slow cleaner, so it took me around ten or twelve hours to clean. Oh well, it was worth it. I love when my room is clean, I just hate cleaning it.

I'm heading to Minnesota with Squeaky on Friday. I can't wait. I loved the trip last year. I hope this year it will be just as good. No one should bother to call me (not like anyone ever does anyway), because I won't have my phone. It's no use having a Cricket phone outside of the valley.

My summer has sucked, other than hanging out with Squeaky and going to San Francisco. I kind of wish school would start again. There is about a month and a half left of summer. It just needs to be done with.

It seems to me like Squeaky is my only friend. He's the only person that ever wants to hang out with me. No one really talks to me anymore. I haven't talked to some people in weeks. It annoys me, especially when those people said, "We should definitely hang out this summer." How can we hang out if they don't even talk to me?

I'm gonna start keeping a personal journal. I've tried before, but it hasn't worked out. Maybe it will this time.

Ish tries to sleep: Take 2.

I don't want to be here anymore.

Everyone hates me.

My mom just told me to go back to Bridgeport where I belong, because I don't belong here.

I want to go somewhere far away so I don't have to see her or my brothers ever again.

I hate being at home..

I'm hungry.. even though I just had a can of Ravioli stuffs. I want more food.

I'm becoming obsessed with Hoobastank's first album. I love it.

My keyboard doesn't have a spacebar.. Somehow, it disappeared. It has to be on my floor somewhere.. I don't feel like looking for it right now.

My mom actually told me to get out of bed this morning. I didn't think she cared about how long I stayed in bed.

I had Fruity Pebbles when I woke up. I regretted it, though. It made me feel sick for a little while. That always happens when I eat cereal.. I wonder why.

I played Gamecube for a little while today. And looked for more stuff to draw.

Speaking of drawing.. I know what I'm drawing next. I will draw Naru Narusegawa from Love Hina.

It's always so hot in my room..

I got a haircut today. It's too short.

I've taken up drawing for fun again. Last night, I drew Cloud Strife from Final Fantasy VII, and earlier today I drew Tifa Lockheart, also from Final Fantasy VII. I must say, I'm very proud of myself. I did a great job drawing them. I'm going to draw other Final Fantasy VII characters, and other things, too, which I haven't thought of yet.

I want to go to a concert.

I'm not getting a season pass for Big Surf or Sunsplash this summer. My mom doesn't have the money to pay for any, and of course, I don't either. I don't even see the point of getting one. Last summer I went to Big Surf once, and that's it. Huge waste of a season pass. I probably won't be going at all this summer.

I think the rest of this summer is going to suck.

Never mind the face that you put on
In front of me.
Never mind the pain you put me through.
Every little thing you say,
And every little thing you do
Makes me doubt all of this.

What are you waiting for?

Look what you did.
Is this who you wanted me to be?
It's not me, no.
Look what you did.
Is this how you wanted it to be?
This life you gave away
Was meant for me.

Forget about this trip you've been on
Or so it seems.
Never mind the lies you told my tears.
Every little thing you said,
And every little thing you did
Made me doubt all of this.

Is that what you're waiting for?

Look what you did.
Is this who you wanted me to be?
It's not me, no.
Look what you did.
Is this how you wanted it to be?
This life you gave away
Was meant for me.

Look at me! I'm back to LJ.

School ended about a week and a half ago. I'm so glad it's over. I want to see my grades! I haven't gotten my report card yet.

I've been very bored, though.. I haven't really done much yet. It's kind of hard to do anything without any way to get around. I'm going with Squeaky to San Francisco, though, so that should be lots of fun. I don't know when we're going, though.

I've been feeling pretty crappy lately..
If you don't know yet, I have a new blog. Ish's new blog.
I want everyone to comment anonymously with a confession, secret, or just a thought. I've disabled IP logging so you can keep it safe. :Ish:
Well, I've decided to make my journal a friends only journal. So too bad to you people who aren't my friends.
